us</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705193,"age":4,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Agness de Climpsfold de Weston was born about 1333, in Slinfold, Sussex, England, her father, Elis de Climsfield, was 44 and her mother, Agnes Dunstavell, was 34. She had at least 4 sons with William de Weston. She died after 1357."},"et":{"about 1333–after 1357":"umbes 1333–pärast 1357","1333–1357":"1333–1357","1327–Male":"1327–Surnud","1330–1418":"1330–1418","1360–Male":"1360–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1290–1390":"1290–1390","1300–1400":"1300–1400","1330":"1330","1360":"1360","1390":"1390","1290":"1290","after 1357":"pärast 1357","1327":"1327","1337":"1337","1357":"1357","1400":"1400","1300":"1300","1333":"1333","1453":"1453","about 1332":"umbes 1332","about 1333":"umbes 1333","1418":"1418","Surrey, England":"Surrey, England","Slinfold, Sussex, England":"Slinfold, Sussex, England"},"fi":{"about 1333–after 1357":"noin 1333–1357 jälkeen","1333–1357":"1333–1357","1327–Male":"1327–Kuollut","1330–1418":"1330–1418","1360–Male":"1360–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1290–1390":"1290–1390","1300–1400":"1300–1400","1330":"1330","1360":"1360","1390":"1390","1290":"1290","after 1357":"1357 jälkeen","1327":"1327","1337":"1337","1357":"1357","1400":"1400","1300":"1300","1333":"1333","1453":"1453","about 1332":"noin 1332","about 1333":"noin 1333","1418":"1418","Surrey, England":"Surrey, England","Slinfold, Sussex,